---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
const faqs = [
  { q: 'What counts as a blank line?', a: 'A line that is empty or contains only whitespace (spaces or tabs) is considered blank and will be removed.' },
  { q: 'Will it remove lines that have only spaces?', a: 'Yes — lines containing only spaces or tabs are treated as blank and removed.' },
  { q: 'Is there a limit on how many lines I can process?', a: 'No — you can paste as much text as needed. All blank lines are removed in one operation.' },
  { q: 'Will the line order change?', a: 'No — only blank lines are removed. The order of all non-blank lines is preserved exactly.' },
];
---
<BlogLayout
  title="How to Remove Blank Lines from Text Online Free"
  description="Remove all empty and blank lines from text instantly. Paste your text, click copy, done. Free online blank line remover — no signup needed."
  canonical="/blog/how-to-remove-blank-lines-from-text-online"
  date="2026-07-02"
  readTime="2 min read"
  category="Text Utilities"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p>Empty lines in copied text can be annoying — especially when pasted from PDFs, websites, or code editors. This tool strips all blank lines instantly, leaving only the lines that have actual content.</p>

  <h2>How to Remove Blank Lines</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Paste your text into the input box.</li>
    <li>All blank lines are removed automatically in real time.</li>
    <li>Copy the output.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>When to Use This Tool</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Cleaning up text pasted from PDFs</li>
    <li>Removing extra blank lines from copied web content</li>
    <li>Preparing data files (CSV, TSV) with consistent formatting</li>
    <li>Cleaning code or configuration files</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="my-8 p-5 bg-violet-950/40 border border-violet-800/50 rounded-2xl text-center">
    <p class="text-slate-300 mb-3">Remove all blank lines instantly — free, no signup</p>
    <a href="/tools/remove-blank-lines" class="inline-block bg-violet-600 hover:bg-violet-500 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-xl transition-colors">Open Remove Blank Lines Tool →</a>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
